Started out with the two argument approach like so -
return set.select(this::contains, this.newEmpty());
Since the same won't work on the immutable side, I leaned towards symmetry. I will update the implementation on the mutable side to use select with a target empty collection and leave the lazy implementation on the immutable side. Let me know if that is good.

